  "status": "Final",
  "summary": "This is a standard for semi-fungible tokens. The set of smart contract interfaces described in this document defines an [ERC-721](./eip-721.md) compatible token standard. This standard introduces an `<ID, SLOT, VALUE>` triple scalar model that represents the semi-fungible structure of a token. It also introduces new transfer models as well as approval models that reflect the semi-fungible nature of the tokens. Token contains an ERC-721 equivalent ID property to identify itself as a universally unique entity, so that the tokens can be transferred between addresses and approved to be operated in ERC-721 compatible way. Token also contains a `value` property, representing the quantitative nature of the token. The meaning of the 'value' property is quite like that of the 'balance' property of",
  "title": "Semi-Fungible Token"
}